<dl id="n05014i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05014i">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05014i"> 14(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> (Eve f &mdash; by ape</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On the other hand, there is a dirty Jewish legend, mentioned by Bayle, which represents <mark>Eve as being seduced by a lascivious monkey</mark>. Christian legends have been equally insulting. An early sect declared that Eve had Cain and Abel, not by her husband, but by a monstrous intercourse with the Devil. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Eve and the Apple]37-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
